      "source": ["import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\nprint('Directional statistics module loaded')"]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": ["## Circular Mean\n**Problem**: Average of angles (e.g., 359° and 1°)\n**Solution**: Use circular mean"]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": ["angles_deg = np.array([350, 10, 5, 355, 0])\nangles_rad = np.radians(angles_deg)\n\nprint('Circular Mean\\n')\nprint(f'Angles: {angles_deg}°')\nprint(f'Arithmetic mean: {angles_deg.mean():.1f}° (WRONG)')\n\n# Circular mean\nfrom scipy.stats import circmean\ncirc_mean = circmean(angles_rad)\ncirc_mean_deg = np.degrees(circ_mean) % 360\nprint(f'Circular mean: {circ_mean_deg:.1f}° (CORRECT)')"]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": ["## Von Mises Distribution\n**Description**: Circular analog of normal\n**Parameters**: μ (mean direction), κ (concentration)"]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": ["mu, kappa = 0, 2\nvm = stats.vonmises(kappa, loc=mu)\nsamples = vm.rvs(size=100)\n\nprint(f'Von Mises(μ={mu}, κ={kappa})\\n')\nprint(f'Generated {len(samples)} samples')\ncirc_mean_sample = circmean(samples)\nprint(f'Sample circular mean: {np.degrees(circ_mean_sample):.1f}°')"]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": ["## Real Example: Wind Direction Analysis\n**Data**: Wind directions over time"]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": ["print('Wind Direction Analysis\\n')\nnp.random.seed(42)\n# Prevailing wind from NW (315°)\nwind_dirs = np.random.vonmises(np.radians(315), 3, 100)\nwind_dirs_deg = (np.degrees(wind_dirs) % 360)\n\nprint(f'Observations: {len(wind_dirs)}')\nprint(f'Range: {wind_dirs_deg.min():.1f}° to {wind_dirs_deg.max():.1f}°')\n\nmean_dir = np.degrees(circmean(wind_dirs)) % 360\nprint(f'\\nMean direction: {mean_dir:.1f}°')\nprint(f'  (Prevailing from {"NW" if 270 < mean_dir < 360 else "?"})\\n')\n\n# Concentration\nfrom scipy.stats import circvar\ncirc_var = circvar(wind_dirs)\nprint(f'Circular variance: {circ_var:.4f}')\nprint(f'  (Low variance = consistent direction)')"]
